Status update:

The [atlas_shim_interface branch](#!/osrf/drcsim/src/07583931db69f1f1a4571ec8888f84a69b24f34b/?at=atlas_shim_interface) compiles a shim library against headers that are AtlasSimInterface 2.10.2 compatible. The goal is that one can drop in the official BDI supplied `libAtlasSimInterface.so` over the [shim `libAtlasSimInterace.so`](#!/osrf/drcsim/src/07583931db69f1f1a4571ec8888f84a69b24f34b/drcsim_model_resources/AtlasSimInterface_2.10.2/src/AtlasSimInterface.cc?at=atlas_shim_interface) and will be able to control the robot with the new behaviors.

The controller is not behaving correctly right now, we are debugging at this point.

